{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Chrono::ROS: A bridge that enables Chrono to interact with the autonomy stack or sensor infrastructure of robots using ROS2. 5.",
    "Chrono::Sensor: Provides sensor modeling and simulation. 6.",
    "Chrono::DEM: Enables the simulation of discrete element method problems, with a focus on granular materials. 7.",
    "Chrono::CRM: supports terramechanics simulations enabling one to model the interaction between a deformable terrain and a robot, vehicle, or rover. 8.",
    "Chrono::Parsers: A tool to import external models and to interact with other languages, e.g., URDF.hardware-in-the-loop simulations [22], wind turbine dynamics [23,24], hydrodynamics [25] and oil industry applications [26].As of Jun 2025, Project Chrono has been developed for more than 25 years and iterated to its 9.0.0 version."
  ],
